This file is not distributed with the program. It outlines some notes for
developers readying a set of files for distribution.

CVS CHECKOUT:
$ export CVS_RSH=ssh
$ cvs -z3 -d:ext:coppit@cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/yagg co devel

Checklist for a release:
- Be sure to add new test cases for new features
- Make sure version number increases.
- Add version changes to README and CHANGES, anonymizing the notes in the
  README.
- Add new module dependencies to Makefile.PL, and update README
- Update MANIFEST and MANIFEST.SKIP if necessary.
  $ make distcheck
- Test your distribution:
  $ make realclean
  $ perl Makefile.PL
  $ make
  $ make test
- Test the speed of the new code:
  - make testspeed
- After the tests have passed, make the distribution file:
  $ make dist
- Install the distribution file elsewhere to test it.
  $ scp yagg-X.XX.tar.gz coppit@linux.sourceforge.net:.
  $ ssh -l coppit linux.sourceforge.net
  $ tar xvfz yagg-X.XX.tar.gz
  $ cd yagg-X.XX
  $ perl Makefile.PL
  $ make
  $ make test
- Update CHANGES file, and copy to server:
  $ scp CHANGES coppit@yagg.sourceforge.net:yagg/htdocs
  (Use your username instead of coppit)
- Upload to CPAN:
    http://pause.perl.org/pause/authenquery
  or
    cpan-upload yagg-X.XX.tar.gz
- Release file:
  http://sourceforge.net/account/login.php
  ncftpput upload.sf.net incoming yagg-X.XX.tar.gz
  http://sourceforge.net/project/admin/editpackages.php?group_id=126089
- Announce any news on SourceForge:
  http://sourceforge.net/news/submit.php?group_id=126089
- Announce on freshmeat:
  http://freshmeat.net/login/
  [search for yagg, select add release]
- Announce it to yagg-announce@sourceforge.net and to
  comp.lang.perl.announce.
- Check in code:
  $ cvs ci
- Tag the release for easy retrieval later
  $ cvs tag "v1_2100"
- Make a backup in old
  $ cvs -z3 -d:ext:coppit@cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/yagg export -d old -r v5_20_0 devel
